==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[payle]]'' 'wooden container', from {{etyl|ang}} ''[[pægel|pæġel]]'' 'wine vessel, container for liquids, pail; liquid measure', from {{proto|Germanic|pagilaz|lang=en}} 'peg, rake' (compare {{etyl|dum|-}}/{{etyl|gml|-}} ''[[pegel#Middle Dutch|pegel]]'' 'half pint', {{etyl|da|-}} ''{{l|da|pægel}}'' 'id.'), diminutive of *''pag-''. More at [[peg]].

